The paper investigates the effectiveness of deep neural networks in modeling dynamical systems with complex behavior, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with system identification, which falls under the category of control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses deep neural networks, which are a type of neural network, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on publicly available datasets, which falls under the category of data mining, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) another possible sub-category.
